narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This is a decent course, but the value of it depends greatly on the teacher. It is often tedious reading, but the classes themselves are interesting.

I would recommend this course. If you are looking to develop your French skills in college, this course is an important stepping-stone. If you simply are interested in learning more about contemporary France, I think the course is equally valuable.

Yep, I would recommend it. Bear in mind that you will have to turn in assignments every day, and it can get kind of tedious. Make sure you get a good teacher (like M. Lamy, who very kindly didn't mind when I forgot to do my homework) and a good class (smaller is better in a conversation class).
A great class that focuses on oral french. A fair amount of work (daily writing/reading/listening assignments, but it is worth it. Take it if the teacher is good.
